The following folks are the primary maintainers of Mailman:

	John Viega, Mailman's inventor
	Ken Manheimer, Mailman's savior
	Barry Warsaw, Mailman's yappy guard dog (and current hydrant pisser)
	Scott Cotton, Cookie-Monster
	Harald Meland

They can be contacted directly via mailman-cabal@python.org.

Here is the list of other contributors who have donated large bits of
code, and have assigned copyright for this code to the FSF:

	The Dragon De Monsyne

Thanks also to Dragon for his winning Mailman logo contribution!

Here is a list of authors of separate modules which are currently
distributed with Mailman, but are not part of Mailman:

	Timothy O'Malley, author of misc/Cookie.py.  This file is
	distributed under the GNU LGPL, and is included in the Mailman
	distribution for convenience only.  It is not part of Mailman.

Here is the list of other people who have contributed useful
ideas, suggestions, bug fixes, testing, etc.:

	Balazs Nagy
	Michael Mclay
	Greg Stein
	Gergely Madarasz
	Andrew Kuchling
	Jeff Hahn
	Everyone else on mailman-developers@python.org
	    and mailman-users@python.org!

Thank you, all!


